rComments: One of my fav profs, definitely made me appreciate plants a lot more. Test content is predictable and no surprises. Clear grading criteria for the lab and relaxed atmosphere. Starr is incredibly kind and very funny. Get started on your herbarium early and this class will be something to look forward to! Hope he finds his Dr Starr soda one day

Très bon prof pour les cours en personne. Ses examens sont tous à choix multiple, réponse courte et associations (pas de questions longues), et très courts compte tenu du temps donné. Il nous a aussi fait faire un rapport de biodiversité sur une plante/fungi de notre choix. I will never look at plants the same way again after his class! :)

Dr. Starr is one of my all-time faves!! He managed to make plants cool and interesting lol. HIs exams and one team assignment were not hard. Furthermore, he was always open and willing to listen to you. 10/10 prof but a 100000000/10 person. Truly a gem!
I love going to class just for the stories. All the info is on the slides.

His midterm isn't that hard, even though Dr Starr could've made it pretty difficult: there's just a lot of information to memorize. The lab part was pretty rough though, with Dr Guillet: lab every week and lab report to send 72 hours after. Most of the times, labs were too long so we had to rush in order to finish & lab documents weren't clear.

A solid prof, likes making jokes about plants. The final was non-cumulative for those who passed the midterm, and the expectations for the midterm in terms of course content weren't entirely clear, so study everything on the slides in all its little details. Skipping class is fine since he basically reads off slides, but I wouldn't recommend it.
Lectures are entertaining but perhaps not very informative. All the information is on the slides.

Starr is such a gem. He's funny and really really loves plants! He tries to make a class that many fear enjoyable. The tests are very specific and are fill in the blank/MC. He kinda straight up tells you that you need to memorize parts. Everything you need to know are on his slides, but the tests are very fair. Would DEFINITELY take again

Fantastic prof! Exams are easy if you study well the pdf. Lab preparation and reports take some time. Really interesting! He gives useful examples and cool stories about his job. Easy going and funny. Everything you need to know is in the pdf. The information he adds are usually just a plus, but not worth studying, except for the arctic chapter.

The textbook is useless, everything is on the pdf. Memorise all the presentation content and you will suceed exams. Assisting class is useless. He's a natural humorist, you will laugh for sure with him!

Julian is a funny and great lecturer.  His midterm and exam were pretty fair. The assignment was super easy. No textbook was used for this class, everything was on his slides which was a huge bonus. He's very approachable, he encourages his students to go to his office hours to talk to him. The labs were easy, but tough markers. Beware lab quizzes.

Was hilarious and really personable. Do not buy the textbook-is a waste of money. Midterm and final were fill in the blank style so you have to know the content well. Labs were long but helped solidify concepts from lectures. Not a fan of plants but its clear Dr. Starr was and therefore the class was enjoyable because of his clear passion.

Buying the textbook was a waste of money and time. Put all your energy into memorizing the slides, everything you need to do well are there. In my opinion his exams were very fair and straight forward even though he could make them really difficult if he wanted to. Didn't go to class often but when I did I found him so funny and weird- I loved him.

Dr. Starr is a really caring and nice prof, he cares or his students even if he doesn't really get the chance to meet them. He is almost always available at his office when his door is open. His tests are shot answer and multiple choice, I have not found them hard, the questions are very straight forward. Recommend for sure! Labs are hard though

his lectures are pretty easy, he tells a lot of stories and is a really funny guy. his tests are really easy too, barely need to ever write a sentence. as long as you grasp what is going on in the slides, theres really nothing to it.
j'ai trouvé ses lectures très ennuyant et il n'explique pas très bien la matière.  J'avais besoin de référer au manuel plusieurs fois car il se contredit beaucoup.
cool guy

His class is all about regurgitating information on the tests. For the midterm he just said to learn everything on all his powerpoints by heart. In class, I felt like I didn't understand what he was talking about at least half of the time. The labs are a real pain; hard questions, and very difficult to get good grades on.

Awesome class, prof is approachable and tells funny stories! If you attend class, there's no reason you shouldn't be able to answer the test questions. The labs are fun too if you like botany, and if you follow the instructions for the project, it's an easy grade!  I hope someone can find that cola he's been after...

Decent class, decent prof, usual bio class, not a super tough grader but you need to know your stuff coming into exams. Lots of information to memorize like any other bio class. Dont really need to go to class to succeed, LAB is garbage tho. Every week, 3 hours and very hard to get good grades in
Extraordinary prof.

I loved both the class and the prof!!!! Yes, it's lots of work, but it is worth it. Prof always brings interesting plants, funny stories, love for botany and his enthusiasm to class. I wish all my profs were like him. Helpful, caring, good at explaining stuff, interested in his subject AND able to interest others in it. THE BEST PROF of university!
super cool and full of enthousiasm... really liked him and his class and his cocots (pine cones) as he would put it... he`s funny to boot in his own way.

BEST PROF EVER!!!! good teaching style, great notes with many pictures (that actually help to understand concepts), very fair tests. EXTREMELY enthusiastic. brings in interesting things (huge cones, weird seeds, etc.) he definetely conveys his love for botany! my absolutelly favorite class and prof!!! i hope to take Dr. Starr's classes in future.

Really enthusiastic about what he's teaching. Lots of office hours and explains really well. His slides are great and easy to learn from. He sometimes brings cool stuff to class (cool/weird "food", giant pinecones, fossils). If you study, you will be rewarded; the tests are really fair but you still need to study. I highly recommend this prof!
I find Julian to be a very passionate teacher who is extremely knowledgeable about botany. This class is a lot of work, but all biology classes are !!
Funny guy, really nice. Liked the lecture. Lab portion with Dr. Heinerman was hard. Like the the class a lot more than I expected to.
